<!-- wp:image -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://sugoii-japan.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Lifestyle-in-Japan-Kabukicho-Night-Shinjuku-1024x600.jpg" alt=""/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>On the outside, it looks as though it’s the perfect place to live. It’s easy to admire the perfect balance between the future – Japan boasts some of the world’s most technologically advanced systems; the present – the social, arts, food and drinks, and entertainment culture is rivalled by none; and past – they’re a proud country with strong roots to their traditions and their history is still evident almost everywhere you look.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Fun Fact: Did you know that the population of Japan also boasts some of the world’s oldest living people on the Okinawan Islands?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":5011,"linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://pinterest.com/pin/create/bookmarklet/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsugoii-japan.com%2Flifestyle-in-japan&amp;media=data%3Aimage%2Fsvg%2Bxml%2C%253Csvg%2520xmlns%3D%2522http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%2522%2520width%3D%2522512%2522%2520height%3D%2522768%2522%253E%253C%2Fsvg%253E&amp;description=Lifestyle%20in%20Japan%20-%20Okinawa%20islands&amp;is_video=false" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img src="https://sugoii-japan.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Lifestyle-in-Japan-Okinawa-islands.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:512x768/rscb1/ng:webp/ngcb1" alt="Lifestyle in Japan - Okinawa islands" class="wp-image-5011" title="Lifestyle in Japan - Okinawa islands"/></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You’ve seen the stunning photos online, watched the popular Japanese dramas with incredibly gorgeous leads, and binged on the anime series that everyone seems to be talking about. But how much of that actually gives you insight into what the lifestyle is <em>really </em>like in Japan?</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Travelling around the country and absorbing pop-culture in your spare time is one thing, but actually living the day-to-day lifestyle in Japan is completely different!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Many people experience a bit of a culture shock when they try to settle down in Japan. Whilst most will quickly adapt and move on, the lingering feeling of outsider-ness might stick around for a while.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We’ve detailed below some fun, interesting, and enlightening information about the lifestyle in Japan for you to read and try to understand it a bit better.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
